core.name: Party Group
core.description: Party group is the category to which the party belongs. A group is an informal structure of persons or organizations, such as a household, a special interest or advocacy group, or a project group. Individual parties can be grouped if they are affiliated together and you want to treat them as a separate entity. A party can belong to one or more groups depending on the rules defined for categorizing the parties. For example, a household is a set of persons (parties) who are extended members of the same family, and who can be treated as a unit for certain purposes, such as marketing.

core.name: Party
core.description: Party is a person or an organization and is the main entity in the data model. Parties have characteristics, such as names, phone numbers, addresses, and taxation details. In a business-to- customer (B2C) scenario, a person is a customer. In a business-to-business (B2B) scenario, an organization is the customer. Not all parties are customers. A party can be a related organization or contact. Related organizations or a contacts might be potential customers. You do not capture the same level of detail for a related organization or a contact as you would for a customer role.
